1. Sample usage - 
        To build an index - python build_index.py -i -b -d books/                 //the index is stored in a file named index_file
        To load an index from an existing file - python build_index.py -f "index_file"


Detailed usage - 
Usage: build_index.py [options]

Options:
-h, --help            show this help message and exit
-d DIR_NAME, --directory=DIR_NAME
directory in which the documents exist
-b                    store index in a file or not
-i                    create an index
-f INDEX_FILE, --index_file=INDEX_FILE
read index from the file
